### The `.liquid-card` Class
This is the fundamental atom of the interface.
```css
.liquid-card {
  /* The Substance */
  background: oklch(0.20 0 0 / 0.4); /* Translucent Obsidian */
  backdrop-filter: blur(24px) saturate(140%); /* Heavy Blur + Vibration */
  
  /* The Edge */
  border: 1px solid oklch(1 0 0 / 0.08); /* "Liquid Mercury" Rim */
  box-shadow: 
    0 4px 24px -1px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.2), /* Soft Drop */
    inset 0 1px 0 0 oklch(1 0 0 / 0.05); /* Top Specular Highlight */
    
  /* The Feel */
  border-radius: 1.5rem; /* rounded-3xl */
  transition: all 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.4, 0, 1); /* Fluid Physics */
}

.liquid-card:hover {
  background: oklch(0.22 0 0 / 0.5);
  border-color: oklch(1 0 0 / 0.15);
  transform: translateY(-2px) scale(1.005);
  box-shadow: 
    0 20px 40px -4px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.4),
    inset 0 1px 0 0 oklch(1 0 0 / 0.1); /* Brighter Reflection */
}
```

## 5. TYPOGRAPHY: KINETIC & VARIABLE
Text is not static ink; it is light emitted from the screen.
- **Font Family:** `Geist Sans` (The Vercel Standard) or `Inter Variable`.
- **Headings:** Tight tracking (`tracking-tight`), high contrast (`text-ink-primary`).
- **Data/Code:** `Geist Mono` for all numbers, IDs, and tabular data.
- **Hierarchy:**
  - `H1`: `text-4xl font-light tracking-tighter text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-white/60` (Simulated reflection).
  - `Body`: `text-sm font-normal text-ink-muted`.

